# Controller-Based Test Rules

* Create one test file per controller.
* File naming convention:

```text
<ControllerName>_test.ts
```

Examples:

```text
Activities_test.ts
Authors_test.ts
Books_test.ts
Users_test.ts
```

* Each controller test file must contain tests for all endpoints under that controller.
* Group tests using Playwright `test.describe()` blocks.

Example:

```typescript
test.describe('Activities Controller', () => {
});
```

---

# Test Data Rules

* Store test data separately from test scripts.
* Create dedicated JSON files under the `testData` folder.
* Never hardcode request bodies inside test files unless unavoidable.
* Support:

  * Positive data
  * Negative data
  * Boundary data
  * Invalid data

Example:

```json
{
  "validActivity": {},
  "invalidActivity": {},
  "boundaryActivity": {}
}
```

---

# API Validation Rules

Every endpoint must validate:

## Functional Validation

* Response status code
* Response headers
* Content-Type
* Response body
* Required fields
* Optional fields
* Response schema
* Data types
* Enum values
* Pagination
* Sorting
* Filtering

---

## CRUD Validation

For Create endpoints:

* Successful creation
* Duplicate record handling
* Missing mandatory fields
* Invalid payload

For Read endpoints:

* Get all records
* Get by ID
* Get invalid ID
* Get non-existing ID

For Update endpoints:

* Successful update
* Partial update
* Invalid update payload
* Update non-existing resource

For Delete endpoints:

* Successful delete
* Delete already deleted record
* Delete invalid ID

---

# Status Code Validation

Validate all applicable responses:

```text
200 OK
201 Created
202 Accepted
204 No Content
400 Bad Request
401 Unauthorized
403 Forbidden
404 Not Found
405 Method Not Allowed
409 Conflict
415 Unsupported Media Type
422 Validation Error
429 Too Many Requests
500 Internal Server Error
502 Bad Gateway
503 Service Unavailable
```

---

# Schema Validation Rules

* Validate every response against Swagger schema.
* Fail test if:

  * Required fields are missing.
  * Additional unexpected fields appear.
  * Data types do not match.
  * Enum values are invalid.

---

# Performance Validation Rules

Capture:

* Response time
* DNS lookup time (if available)
* Connection time
* SSL handshake time (if available)
* Payload size
* Request size

Validate:

```text
GET < 2000ms
POST < 3000ms
PUT < 3000ms
DELETE < 3000ms
```

Flag slower responses as warnings.

---

# Reliability Rules

Implement:

* Automatic retries for transient failures.
* Request timeout handling.
* Network failure validation.
* Service unavailable validation.
* Graceful error logging.

---

# Security Validation Rules

Validate:

* Missing authentication token
* Invalid authentication token
* Expired token
* Invalid content type
* Injection attempts
* XSS payloads
* SQL injection patterns
* Header manipulation
* Large payload handling

Never log secrets, passwords, API keys, or tokens.

---

# Data Management Rules

* Generate unique test data dynamically.
* Avoid test data collisions.
* Support cleanup after execution.
* Ensure tests are independent and repeatable.
* Do not rely on execution order.

---

# Logging Rules

Capture for every request:

* Endpoint URL
* HTTP method
* Query parameters
* Request headers
* Request payload
* Response headers
* Response payload
* Status code
* Response time
* Timestamp
* Correlation ID (if available)

Store logs separately from reports.

---

# Reporting Rules

## HTML Report Requirements

Always generate a standalone HTML report.

Location:

```text
reports/
```

Features:

* Responsive design
* Modern dark theme
* Dashboard layout
* Professional UI
* Mobile-friendly design

---

## Dashboard Widgets

Display:

* Total Tests
* Passed
* Failed
* Skipped
* Warnings
* Success Rate
* Average Response Time
* Fastest Endpoint
* Slowest Endpoint
* Total Execution Time
* Add more parameters using best practices for reports
* Add bar chart or 3-D Pie diagram  

---

## Endpoint Detail View

Every endpoint result must be expandable.

Display:

* Endpoint URL
* HTTP Method
* Controller Name
* Request Body
* Request Headers
* Response Body
* Response Headers
* Status Code
* Response Time
* Payload Size
* Test Result
* Failure Reason
* Screenshot (if applicable)

---

## Visual Indicators

Use:

* Green → Passed
* Red → Failed
* Amber → Warning
* Blue → Information

Include:

* Charts
* Progress bars
* Status badges
* Summary tiles
* Execution trends

---

# Failure Handling Rules

On failure:

* Capture complete request details.
* Capture complete response details.
* Capture stack trace.
* Capture validation error details.
* Continue execution of remaining tests.

---

# Maintainability Rules

* No duplicated logic.
* Reusable API clients.
* Reusable validation helpers.
* Centralized configuration.
* Environment-based execution.
* Configurable base URLs.
* Configurable credentials.

---

# CI/CD Rules

Framework must support:

* GitHub Actions
* Azure DevOps
* GitLab CI
* Jenkins

Generate:

* HTML reports
* JUnit reports
* JSON reports

Artifacts must be publishable by CI pipelines.

---

# Coverage Rules

The final automation suite must achieve:

* 100% Endpoint Coverage
* 100% Controller Coverage
* Positive Test Coverage
* Negative Test Coverage
* Schema Validation Coverage
* Error Handling Coverage
* Reporting Coverage

No endpoint defined in Swagger may remain untested.
